ign: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 485px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						&nbsp;</div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-time" style="margin: 0px; padding: 8px 3px 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: auto; height: 17px; line-height: 11px; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); overflow: hidden; text-align: center; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						&nbsp;</div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-button mejs-volume-button mejs-mute" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; position: relative; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 26px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						<button aria-controls="mep_1" style="cursor: pointer; display: block; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0; margin: 7px 5px; padding: 0px; position: absolute; height: 16px; width: 16px; border: 0px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/controls.png); background-position: -16px -16px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;" title="Mute Toggle" type="button"></button></div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-button mejs-fullscreen-button" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 26px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						<button aria-controls="mep_1" style="cursor: pointer; display: block; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0; margin: 7px 5px; padding: 0px; position: absolute; height: 16px; width: 16px; border: 0px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/controls.png); background-position: -32px 0px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;" title="Fullscreen" type="button"></button></div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="mejs-clear" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both;">\r\n					&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<span class="video-download" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 9px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.fxguide.com/download/?force_file=/2013/07/trainfight.mp4" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none;">Download Video</a></span></div>\r\n	<hr class="clear" style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 640px; height: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none; font-size: 1px; line-height: 0px; padding: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" />\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Watch part of the final sequence.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	It was decided, then, that actors and stunt performers on wires would be filmed on a set piece surrounded by greenscreen. For what would be viewable beyond the train, Hill notes that the filmmakers wanted to see a lot of depth in the backgrounds, not just a few CG buildings. But the sequence would span nearly two and a half minutes of footage &ndash; a significant city build for that length.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	That led to a decision to shoot backgrounds practically as much as possible, both for actually filling out the sequence and for reference. &ldquo;The overall VFX supe Phil Brennan had this great idea,&rdquo; says Hill, &ldquo;where he said, &lsquo;Why don&rsquo;t we look at filming, rather than on a train, but on an elevated freeway that&rsquo;s going through Tokyo.&rsquo; So we scouted some locations and found this elevated freeway in Shinjuku. We can drive up and down that all day and get lots of plates.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	However, at that point in the production the actual shots had not been designed, so rather than plates the team adopted a &lsquo;Google Streetview method&rsquo;. &ldquo;But instead of having a big panoramic cam on top of a van, we built a rig that had eight 45 degree angle RED EPICs that gave us massive resolution driving down all the massive lanes of the freeway,&rdquo; explains Hill. &ldquo;We let a bit of air out of the tires of the van and kept a constant 60 kilometers an hour. So if we shot at 48 fps we just needed to speed up the footage by 10 times to give us the 300 kilometers an hour required.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	The results were moving backgrounds filmed from an elevated position to approximately match the position of the train if it had been filmed for real. &ldquo;We still had to take that footage, line it up for all the shots we wanted to compose to go with our greenscreen backgrounds,&rdquo; says Hill, &ldquo;and then do a lot of one point perspective and two point perspective photogrammetry techniques to re-warp those plates and give them the depth and the nodal point offsets we couldn&rsquo;t get by merely taking the footage and placing it as a background. &rdquo;</p>\r\n<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="margin: 0px auto 20px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 640px;">\r\n	<div class="video-player" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; width: 640px;">\r\n		<div class="mejs-container mejs-video" id="mep_2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, Arial; vertical-align: top; position: relative; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left; width: 640px; height: 360px;">\r\n			<div class="mejs-inner" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				<div class="mejs-mediaelement" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 640px; height: 360px;">\r\n					<div class="me-plugin" id="me_flash_2_container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute;">\r\n						&nbsp;</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="mejs-layers" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n					<div class="mejs-poster mejs-layer" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 640px; height: 360px;">\r\n						<img height="100%" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads//2013/07/train_broll.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block;" width="100%" /></div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-overlay mejs-layer mejs-overlay-play" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; cursor: pointer; width: 640px; height: 360px;">\r\n						<div class="mejs-overlay-button" style="margin: -50px 0px 0px -50px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 180px; left: 320px; width: 100px; height: 100px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/bigplay.png); background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n							&nbsp;</div>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="mejs-controls" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; list-style-type: none; bottom: 0px; left: 0px; background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(50, 50, 50, 0.701961), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.701961)); height: 30px; width: 640px; visibility: hidden;">\r\n					<div class="mejs-button mejs-playpause-button mejs-play" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 26px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						<button aria-controls="mep_2" style="cursor: pointer; display: block; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0; margin: 7px 5px; padding: 0px; position: absolute; height: 16px; width: 16px; border: 0px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/controls.png); background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;" title="Play/Pause" type="button"></button></div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-time-rail" style="margin: 0px; padding: 5px 0px 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 485px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						&nbsp;</div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-time" style="margin: 0px; padding: 8px 3px 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: auto; height: 17px; line-height: 11px; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); overflow: hidden; text-align: center; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						&nbsp;</div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-button mejs-volume-button mejs-mute" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; position: relative; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 26px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						<button aria-controls="mep_2" style="cursor: pointer; display: block; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0; margin: 7px 5px; padding: 0px; position: absolute; height: 16px; width: 16px; border: 0px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/controls.png); background-position: -16px -16px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;" title="Mute Toggle" type="button"></button></div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-button mejs-fullscreen-button" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 26px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						<button aria-controls="mep_2" style="cursor: pointer; display: block; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0; margin: 7px 5px; padding: 0px; position: absolute; height: 16px; width: 16px; border: 0px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/controls.png); background-position: -32px 0px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;" title="Fullscreen" type="button"></button></div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="mejs-clear" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both;">\r\n					&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<span class="video-download" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 9px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.fxguide.com/download/?force_file=/2013/07/train_broll.mp4" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none;">Download Video</a></span></div>\r\n	<hr class="clear" style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 640px; height: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none; font-size: 1px; line-height: 0px; padding: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" />\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		See how the greenscreen portion of the train fight was filmed.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	A major effort was then launched for adding extra components into the shots, things such as roads with moving cars, rush hour traffic, train tracks, gantries, signs, billboards and, of course, the train itself. &ldquo;Jim Mangold was very keen to make the city very Japanese,&rdquo; notes Hill. &ldquo;We showed him the original footage, sped it up and showed it to him and he said it looks great and fast but if you say ignored the bit of text from the car registration plates, you could be almost anywhere. So we had to add lots of colorful billboards showing all manner of noodle bars and train signs.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	&ldquo;And to give it a sense of speed you always want things much closer to camera, so they&rsquo;re really whipping past,&rdquo; adds Hill. &ldquo;So we were lowering all the heights of the gantries so that they would whip over the actors and the camera and give it a sense of speed as the trains go through it. It became a story point as they&rsquo;re always trying to avoid these gantries &ndash; ducking underneath them, interacting and leaping over them.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Weta Digital retained close-up buildings captured with the multi-cam rig, although some were then re-projected onto geometry in Nuke to &ldquo;give us that two point perspective augmentations that we needed to be able to move the camera from where it sat on top of the van,&rdquo; says Hill.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	The back plates were solved first before Jackman and the other actors were filmed on set. The established environment was a little overcast without full sun which the DOP could then match on the greenscreen stage. &ldquo;We&rsquo;d have a keylight replicating the sun,&rdquo; says Hill. &ldquo;There was a giant propeller on a cherry picker with the 10K lights and one of the grips would just revolve it at a certain speed so you&rsquo;d have this light whipping over the background. It was however difficult to get a practical propeller to line up and cast a shadow exactly when Hugh ducks to avoid a gantry. In shots like that we didn&rsquo;t run any kind of shadowing and just did it in post.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" id="attachment_45688" style="margin: 0px auto 20px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 624px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/DF-15352.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="On-set train interior." class="wp-image-45688 " height="409" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/DF-15352-1024x681.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="614" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		On-set train interior.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Ultimately the practical fights and wire work were augmented with digital doubles, especially for some of the more dramatic scenes of the actors leaping to avoid gantries.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Scenes were rendered in RenderMan. &ldquo;We ran a very large environment but kind of a rolling one,&rdquo; explains Hill. &ldquo;So for each shot we&rsquo;d take about a kilometer of track with more or less a standard setup. The first thing we do is render it, see how it looked, judge the speed, or add more drama, adjust the height, the spacing between the gantries. Then we did shot-specific things like if there was a particular gap in the background that had a lovely view to the city we&rsquo;d try and not block that with a giant billboard, or if there was a particularly nasty looking building then we certainly would.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	&ldquo;We also had to think about how are we going to deal with extra bounce lights from buildings that don&rsquo;t exist &ndash; say red buildings &ndash; and how to represent those back onto the train or onto Hugh. They do get fed into an IBL but there&rsquo;s also an element of over-cranking it. We wanted to art direct the lighting and it had to have a certain impact.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<hr style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0.1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.45em; border: none; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;" />\r\n<h3 style="margin: 2em 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 24px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Stomach bug</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement aligncenter" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/THE-WOLVERINE-%C2%A9-2013-20th-CENTURY-FOX-ILOURA.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; clear: both; display: inline-block; position: relative;"><img alt="THE-WOLVERINE---©-2013-20th-CENTURY-FOX---ILOURA" class="aligncenter  wp-image-45763" height="230" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/THE-WOLVERINE-%C2%A9-2013-20th-CENTURY-FOX-ILOURA-1024x384.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto 12px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; display: block;" width="614" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">What happens</em></strong>: A robotic medical beetle is implanted inside Logan&rsquo;s body. When he realizes the parasite is limiting his healing powers, he cuts open his own chest to remove it.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">The challenge</em></strong>: Iloura brought the aggressive tentacled beetle to life both in an appearance in a jar of liquid and as Logan pulls a beetle out of his chest.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	&ldquo;The beetle was modeled in 3ds Max, with a ZBrush sculpt and rigged in Maya,&rdquo; explains Drew Wood-Davies. &ldquo;The tentacles had a keyframe animation component as well as a simulation component. They wanted it to look very aggressive so we had to convey that in the animation.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	On set, Jackman held a small metal prop to simulate its scale as it holds the retrieved beetle. &ldquo;We did a clean-up pass on that and then add in our digital creature,&rdquo; says Wood-Davies. &ldquo;We had to layer things in like blood to make it all sit with the stuff going on.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	For the beetles seen earlier in the jar, Iloura ensured that the caustics gave a small sense of interaction. &ldquo;One of the things we did was have accurate caustic occlusion for the shadows of the beetles on the table in the foreground,&rdquo; notes Wood-Davies, &ldquo;which I felt were quite enjoyable and helped sell the shots.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<hr style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0.1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.45em; border: none; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;" />\r\n<h3 style="margin: 2em 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 24px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Wolverine versus Shingen</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement aligncenter" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_ls-135_comp_v001.1001.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; clear: both; display: inline-block; position: relative;"><img alt="global_marketing_ls-135_comp_v001.1001" class="aligncenter  wp-image-45714" height="257" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_ls-135_comp_v001.1001-1024x428.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto 12px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; display: block;" width="614" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">What happens</em></strong>: After removing the parasitic beetle, Logan fights Shingen who has also been battling Yukio. Shingen is eventually slain.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">The challenge</em></strong>: Rising Sun carried out sword and Wolverine claw replacements for the fight, as well as background composites and rain.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	&ldquo;Shingen had just the sword hilt and we replaced it with a CG sword, including for a shot of him plunging it into Logan,&rdquo; explains Tim Crosbie. &ldquo;Sometimes you can find if you don&rsquo;t have the weight of a full sword and you&rsquo;re miming pushing it in and out, well, the force that actors try and tend to put on with shaking arms make it feel like there&rsquo;s a fair bit of force there. So we had to rebuild the plate behind and stabilize the hand and the sword to sit properly on the sword as it&rsquo;s withdrawn from Wolverine.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" style="margin: 0px auto 20px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 640px;">\r\n	<div class="video-player" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; width: 640px;">\r\n		<div class="mejs-container mejs-video" id="mep_3" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: Helvetica, Arial; vertical-align: top; position: relative; background-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left; width: 640px; height: 360px;">\r\n			<div class="mejs-inner" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				<div class="mejs-mediaelement" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 640px; height: 360px;">\r\n					<div class="me-plugin" id="me_flash_3_container" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute;">\r\n						&nbsp;</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="mejs-layers" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n					<div class="mejs-poster mejs-layer" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 640px; height: 360px;">\r\n						<img height="100%" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads//2013/07/shingenfight.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block;" width="100%" /></div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-overlay mejs-layer mejs-overlay-play" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; cursor: pointer; width: 640px; height: 360px;">\r\n						<div class="mejs-overlay-button" style="margin: -50px 0px 0px -50px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 180px; left: 320px; width: 100px; height: 100px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/bigplay.png); background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;">\r\n							&nbsp;</div>\r\n					</div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="mejs-controls" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; list-style-type: none; bottom: 0px; left: 0px; background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(50, 50, 50, 0.701961), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.701961)); height: 30px; width: 640px; visibility: hidden;">\r\n					<div class="mejs-button mejs-playpause-button mejs-play" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 26px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						<button aria-controls="mep_3" style="cursor: pointer; display: block; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0; margin: 7px 5px; padding: 0px; position: absolute; height: 16px; width: 16px; border: 0px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/controls.png); background-position: 0px 0px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;" title="Play/Pause" type="button"></button></div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-time-rail" style="margin: 0px; padding: 5px 0px 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 485px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						&nbsp;</div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-time" style="margin: 0px; padding: 8px 3px 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: auto; height: 17px; line-height: 11px; color: rgb(255, 255, 255); overflow: hidden; text-align: center; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						&nbsp;</div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-button mejs-volume-button mejs-mute" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; position: relative; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 26px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						<button aria-controls="mep_3" style="cursor: pointer; display: block; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0; margin: 7px 5px; padding: 0px; position: absolute; height: 16px; width: 16px; border: 0px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/controls.png); background-position: -16px -16px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;" title="Mute Toggle" type="button"></button></div>\r\n					<div class="mejs-button mejs-fullscreen-button" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 11px; vertical-align: baseline; list-style-type: none; float: left; width: 26px; height: 26px; line-height: 11px; background-position: 0px 50%;">\r\n						<button aria-controls="mep_3" style="cursor: pointer; display: block; font-size: 0px; line-height: 0; margin: 7px 5px; padding: 0px; position: absolute; height: 16px; width: 16px; border: 0px; background-image: url(http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/themes/fxguide3.1/images/video/controls.png); background-position: -32px 0px; background-repeat: no-repeat no-repeat;" title="Fullscreen" type="button"></button></div>\r\n				</div>\r\n				<div class="mejs-clear" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both;">\r\n					&nbsp;</div>\r\n			</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n			<div class="mejs-fullscreen-hover" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n				&nbsp;</div>\r\n		</div>\r\n		<span class="video-download" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-size: 9px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; display: block; text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.fxguide.com/download/?force_file=/2013/07/shingenfight.mp4" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none;">Download Video</a></span></div>\r\n	<hr class="clear" style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 640px; height: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none; font-size: 1px; line-height: 0px; padding: 0px; background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial;" />\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Watch part of the fight sequence.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Jackman filmed his fight scenes with different sets of claws, depending on the amount of action and interaction required. These were: plastic claw, rubber claws, metal claws and, finally, small two inch long stubs.</p>\r\n<div class="wp-caption alignright" id="attachment_45713" style="margin: 4px 0px 20px 24px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; float: right; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 330px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_ls-135_scan_v001.1001.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Original plate." class="size-medium wp-image-45713" height="133" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_ls-135_scan_v001.1001-320x133.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="320" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Original plate.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	&ldquo;Those metal claws are pretty sharp,&rdquo; observes Crosbie. &ldquo;You can put an eye out pretty easily &ndash; they are polished aluminum. They had to be sharp otherwise they wouldn&rsquo;t play properly in close-up. But only a certain level of stunts can be done with them, beyond which even the slightest bump can cut his knuckles &ndash; so that&rsquo;s where CG takes over.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Multiple still shoots of the claws against black were carried out for reference, and HDRIs also taken. &ldquo;We pulled all that into our asset system,&rdquo; says Crosbie, &ldquo;modeling them in Maya and after it was modeled we did the textures, then based the lighting on HDRIs. We&rsquo;d take a still frame from a plate as the background and spin the claws in the scene, sit them next to the live action ones and see who could tell the difference.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<hr style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0.1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.45em; border: none; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;" />\r\n<h3 style="margin: 2em 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 24px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Village fight</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement aligncenter" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_if-900-x1001_comp_v001.1001.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; clear: both; display: inline-block; position: relative;"><img alt="global_marketing_if-900-x1001_comp_v001.1001" class="aligncenter  wp-image-45722" height="257" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_if-900-x1001_comp_v001.1001-1024x428.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto 12px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; display: block;" width="614" /></a></em></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">What happens</em></strong>: En route to Yashida&rsquo;s lab, Logan is ambushed by Harada&rsquo;s ninjas and battles them in the snow, eventually being pinned down with multiple cabled-arrows and the effect of Viper&rsquo;s venom.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">The challenge</em></strong>: Filmed in summer time at Sydney&rsquo;s Olympic Park, Rising Sun extended the village set and added snow, digital arrows and cables.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	&ldquo;It really was a wonderful set built in Sydney Olympic Park,&rdquo; says Tim Crosbie. &ldquo;We were doing night shoots but it was shot in Sydney in the middle of summer. It was quite a lot of fun, but surreal running around in t-shirts and shorts when it&rsquo;s meant to be the middle of winter in snow.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<hr class="clear" style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none; font-size: 1px; line-height: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif;" />\r\n<div class="wp-caption alignleft" id="attachment_45723" style="margin: 4px 24px 20px 0px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; float: left; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 298px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_if-870_scan_v001.1001.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Original plate." class="wp-image-45723 " height="120" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_if-870_scan_v001.1001-320x133.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="288" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Original plate.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="wp-caption alignright" id="attachment_45724" style="margin: 4px 0px 20px 24px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; float: right; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 298px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_if-870_comp_v001.1001.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Final shot." class="wp-image-45724 " height="120" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/global_marketing_if-870_comp_v001.1001-320x133.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="288" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Final shot.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class="clear" style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none; font-size: 1px; line-height: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif;" />\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	The set was LIDAR&rsquo;d, with RSP carrying out extensions via camera projections onto geo and adding mountains in the far background plus extra snow. Wider views back towards the village from the lab were also realized as matte paintings. The studio handled wounds to Logan&rsquo;s face and claw effects, as well as the green venom into which Harada dips an arrow.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	For the shot of Logan being bombarded with multiple arrows on cables, Jackman was filmed with just a few props attached to his back. &ldquo;We had practical arrows in his back with a few ropes hanging off him,&rdquo; states Crosbie, &ldquo;just to get a good reference for how it should look. Jim wanted certain looks referencing back to the comic framing. The ropes were done using nHair in Maya to get the right flexing and movement.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<hr style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0.1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.45em; border: none; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;" />\r\n<h3 style="margin: 2em 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 24px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Shedding some skin</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement aligncenter" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ss_403_78_236_JL.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; clear: both; display: inline-block; position: relative;"><img alt="ss_403_78_236_JL" class="aligncenter  wp-image-45764" height="230" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ss_403_78_236_JL-1024x384.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto 12px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; display: block;" width="614" /></a></em></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">What happens</em></strong>: Amidst the lab battle taken place between the Silver Samurai and Wolverine, Viper engages in hand-to-hand combat with Yukio. At one point she sheds her snake-like skin.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><strong>The challenge</strong>:</em>&nbsp;Weta Digital produced the effect of Viper ripping off her peeling skin.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Actress Svetlana Khodchenkova mimed the peeling off action. &ldquo;Unfortunately there was no object for resistance for her peeling skin,&rdquo; says Martin Hill, &ldquo;however Svetlana did a great job putting some weight into the performance. Before we started any effect, we re-timed and warped the plate to add more tension to the performance, then worked from that.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Khodchenkova was also filmed with several markers on her skin but, as Hill notes, &ldquo;getting a perfect match under the neck, on the platysma especially was difficult. Once we had that working, we used a combination of two and half D techniques to apply textural and lighting layers onto Viper&rsquo;s skin.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<hr style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0.1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.45em; border: none; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;" />\r\n<h3 style="margin: 2em 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 24px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	A shiny Silver Samurai</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;"><a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement aligncenter" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ss_705_35_87_JL.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; clear: both; display: inline-block; position: relative;"><img alt="ss_705_35_87_JL" class="aligncenter  wp-image-45762" height="230" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/ss_705_35_87_JL-1024x384.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto 12px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; display: block;" width="614" /></a></em></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">What happens</em></strong>: Wolverine confronts a Silver Samurai at the lab made out of adamantium and designed to draw out the mutant&rsquo;s powers of healing.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong><em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">The challenge</em></strong>: Weta Digital brought to life a nine foot tall fully reflective fighting &lsquo;machine&rsquo; that engages in hand-to-hand combat with Hugh Jackman.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	A 3D model of the Silver Samurai had been 3D printed by production and chrome painted using electrolysis methods for use on set. &ldquo;He looked fantastic,&rdquo; noted Martin Hill, &ldquo;but unfortunately he didn&rsquo;t move, so that&rsquo;s where we came in.&rdquo; In addition to creating a &lsquo;living, breathing&rsquo; version of the Samurai, Weta Digital re-worked the original design to ensure it would perform the necessary martial arts moves. &ldquo;The design that had been worked on was very graphic and had a strong presence but it didn&rsquo;t necessarily have all the movements that Jim wanted him to perform,&rdquo; says Hill. &ldquo;For example, he had a very wide chest which would make it difficult to perform traditional Japanese moves, say holding a katanas with two-handed moves.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Stunt performer Shane Rangi stood on stilts during filming as the Silver Samurai. &ldquo;We did dress Shane up in a pseudo mocap suit with witness cameras so we would be able to capture his performance,&rdquo; says Hill. &ldquo;But post-shooting the motion moved much more towards martial arts style and more traditional Japanese style and so we were able to do a lot of keyframing.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<hr class="clear" style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none; font-size: 1px; line-height: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif;" />\r\n<div class="wp-caption alignleft" id="attachment_45832" style="margin: 4px 24px 20px 0px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; float: left; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 298px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ss_795_25_100.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Original plate." class="wp-image-45832 " height="108" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ss_795_25_100-320x120.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="288" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Original plate.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="wp-caption alignright" id="attachment_45829" style="margin: 4px 0px 20px 24px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; float: right; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 298px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ss_795_137_100.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Animation pass." class="wp-image-45829 " height="108" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ss_795_137_100-320x120.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="288" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Animation pass.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" id="attachment_45831" style="margin: 0px auto 20px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 624px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ss_795_100_134_JL.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Final shot." class="wp-image-45831 " height="230" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/ss_795_100_134_JL-1024x384.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="614" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Final shot.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class="clear" style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none; font-size: 1px; line-height: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif;" />\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Animation wise, the Silver Samurai featured a completely solid face mask, so Weta Digital sought to give the character emotion from body performance. &ldquo;There&rsquo;s a point where he stabs his son-in-law and we had to hesitate beforehand &ndash; it had to look like he was doubting himself when he did it, with no eyebrows, no face, no eyes,&rdquo; states Hill.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Perhaps the main challenge for Weta Digital was realizing the Silver Samurai&rsquo;s highly reflective surface. &ldquo;He&rsquo;s pretty much chrome,&rdquo; notes Hill. &ldquo;We were worried that he was going to look incredibly digital and that it was going to be very hard to make him look solid and real and not just like a mirrored surface. So we spent a long time replicating the multi-layered structure of brushed metal with a micro-facet solution to give us an anisotropic patina to him, but also give us a mirrored reflection underneath of the flatter parts in between the grooves. We took the original practical reference on set and had our shader writers actually started machining and milling different bits of metal and having a look at different responses from complicated materials.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	The Silver Samurai also carries a large sword that he is able to heat up and cut through almost any surface, including Wolverine&rsquo;s own adamantium claws. &ldquo;In the original previs the sword had a purple glow around it and left a trail behind it &ndash; almost Japanese anime style,&rdquo; says Hill. &ldquo;It looked cool but once we got into the lookdev of it, Jim wasn&rsquo;t really sure about the ethereal look. We went back to focusing on how katanas are actually made, how they fold them the metal and stick them in to the forge. You get a really interesting heat treatment across the sword while they&rsquo;re forging them &ndash; all the cracked patterns as the layers of the metal are coming away &ndash; you can see it&rsquo;s all based off the temperature of the metal. That&rsquo;s we ended up replicating. Once they&rsquo;ve cooled down they have this thin film interference layer which looks a lot like the color patinas you get around arc welding. Combining these things with the damage during the fight &ndash; it gave him a much more convincing look.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" id="attachment_45766" style="margin: 0px auto 20px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 624px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sd_360_24_328_JL.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Yashida is revealed to be inside the Samurai suit." class="wp-image-45766 " height="230" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sd_360_24_328_JL-1024x384.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="614" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Yashida is eventually revealed to be inside the Samurai suit.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	To replicate the environment, HDRIs were taken at different heights and served as reference for the final environment maps on the Silver Samurai. &ldquo;What that generally gives you is a real representation of what the samurai may have looked like in the scene,&rdquo; says Hill. &ldquo;But the DOP isn&rsquo;t necessarily lighting that dead space where the Samurai is, so we really had to fill in the blanks.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	&ldquo;We designed the lighting more procedurally,&rdquo; continues Hill. &ldquo;Because he&rsquo;s so reflective you can play with parallax in the lighting, so the lights can go behind pillars, say and it&rsquo;s not just the shadow &ndash; you&rsquo;re actually seeing the reflections of the lights disappearing and appearing &ndash; you get real depth.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Hill says Weta Digital had to light the Silver Samurai in a very graphical way. &ldquo;You can&rsquo;t just take a big area bounce light and have it as a crooked angle against those lines &ndash; it needs to be complimentary against his structure and the way he&rsquo;s designed. The lighting needs to be sympathetic to that.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Eventually it is revealed that inside the Silver Samurai is Yashida, kept alive until he believes he can absorb Wolverine&rsquo;s powers. As he attempts to do so, the old Yashida transitions back to his younger self &ndash; a morph completed by Weta Digital which simulated various stages of the transformation. Full FACS sessions with a three-camera setup were undertaken to acquire facial features and gestures. &ldquo;We also recorded the full length of the scene with each actor in each make up stage 2 or 3 times with multiple cameras, which gave us precise reference shapes to aim for rather than always rebuilding from FACS primitive shapes,&rdquo; says Hill.</p>\r\n<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" id="attachment_45768" style="margin: 0px auto 20px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 624px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sd_370_155_300_JL.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Yashida transforms into his young self, momentarily." class="wp-image-45768 " height="230" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/sd_370_155_300_JL-1024x384.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="614" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Yashida transforms into his young self, momentarily.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Artists paid attention to changes required in hair and eyebrows, for example, and the need to adapt sub-surface scattering. &ldquo;Some areas were more translucent and more leathery,&rdquo; explains Hill, &ldquo;so each of those stages were lookdev&rsquo;d independently and then we&rsquo;d be morphing in those individual maps in line with the blendshape transition to always keep the character looking photoreal.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Keeping each point in the transition looking like the actors when blending between was one of Weta Digital&rsquo;s main challenges. &ldquo;Some early tests tended to look like a entirely different character which was neither of the actors,&rdquo; says Hill. &ldquo;The other challenge was to keep the textural and sculptural blends working in tandem without the effect appearing as a wipe.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<strong>Find out more about how Weta Digital completed the Yashida transitions in this&nbsp;<a href="http://www.fxphd.com/blog/de-age-vfx-fxphd-prof-tahl-niran-breaks-down-the-wolverine/" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none;">interview</a>&nbsp;with compositor and fxphd prof. Tahl Niran.</strong></p>\r\n<hr style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0.1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.45em; border: none; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;" />\r\n<h3 style="margin: 2em 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 24px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 1; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Previs&rsquo;ing The Wolverine</h3>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement aligncenter" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/W2_AppvdIm_LoganFlies_071513.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; clear: both; display: inline-block; position: relative;"><img alt="W2_AppvdIm_LoganFlies_071513" class="aligncenter  wp-image-45700" height="346" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/W2_AppvdIm_LoganFlies_071513-1024x576.jpg" style="margin: 0px auto 12px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; display: block;" width="614" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">The Wolverine&rsquo;s</em>&nbsp;previs was handled by Halon Entertainment and supervised by Clint Reagan, who approached the work slightly differently to a typical major comic book film. &ldquo;Jim wanted it to be a more personal,&rdquo; says Reagan. &ldquo;To keep things tighter he didn&rsquo;t want the super big over dramatic exaggerated comic booky stuff. For example, Jim didn&rsquo;t want us to animate something so fantastic that say the stunt guys couldn&rsquo;t even do it, and then it would become an all-CG thing. So we worked really closely with them to do almost like a postvis over their stuntvis work. The stunt guys were able to get just a visceral intensity that would take a whole lot of time in the previs setting. But we could give it so much more context than just in the practical setting of their warehouse.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<div class="wp-caption alignright" id="attachment_45697" style="margin: 4px 0px 20px 24px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; display: inline; float: right; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 330px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/W2_AppvdIm_SS_vs_Logan_071513.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Silver Samurai previs." class="size-medium wp-image-45697" height="180" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/W2_AppvdIm_SS_vs_Logan_071513-320x180.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="320" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Silver Samurai previs.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Halon took the plates of video footage filmed by David Leitch&rsquo;s stunt team and edited and &lsquo;postvis&rsquo;d&rsquo; over the top, which would then serve the second unit and stunt teams during principal photography. Mocap was also relied on early on to flesh out various fight stunt scenes. &ldquo;Fox has a MVN suit from Xsens,&rdquo; notes Reagan, &ldquo;so we went down to David Leitch&rsquo;s stages and they did mocap of some of our scenes that had been blocked out with boards. Then we did some mocap for some martial arts movements. We incorporated a lot of that early on in the Silver Samurai fight, although much of the mocap became obsolete because of the changes required, but it was still great reference.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Some of the major sequences created in previs by Halon were the Nagasaki nuclear bomb, the train fight, Viper&rsquo;s skin reveal, the Silver Samurai encounter and various fight scenes including the funeral, village and a bear sequence that ultimately was cut from the final film. Halon primarily worked in Maya to create previs scenes, using Motion Builder for mocap translation, tracking in SynthEyes, editing in Premiere and added various effects in After Effects.</p>\r\n<div class="wp-caption aligncenter" id="attachment_45696" style="margin: 0px auto 20px; padding: 4px; border: none; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; background-color: rgb(241, 241, 241); color: rgb(136, 136, 136); line-height: 18px; text-align: center; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; width: 624px;">\r\n	<a class="fx_colorbox cboxElement" href="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/W2_AppvdIm_Viper_Face_071513.jpg" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; position: relative; display: inline-block;"><img alt="Viper skin shedding previs." class="wp-image-45696 " height="346" src="http://www.fxguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/W2_AppvdIm_Viper_Face_071513-1024x576.jpg" style="margin: 5px; padding: 0px; border: none; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;" width="614" /></a>\r\n	<p class="wp-caption-text" style="margin: 0px 0px 4px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">\r\n		Viper skin shedding previs.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="sidebox right" style="margin: 0px 0px 10px 30px; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238); border-top-left-radius: 20px; border-top-right-radius: 20px; border-bottom-right-radius: 20px; border-bottom-left-radius: 20px; width: 225.375px; float: right; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px;">\r\n	<strong>Clint Reagan</strong>&nbsp;is also teaching a new course at fxphd called PVS101: Introduction to Previs. Find out more at&nbsp;<a href="http://www.fxphd.com/" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(136, 0, 0); text-decoration: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none;">fxphd.com</a>.</div>\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	Reagan, who once lived in Japan, was able to draw on his personal experiences to previs certain shots, including those set in Nagasaki. &ldquo;The previs was influenced by a woman I met in Japan who lived through the blast in Hiroshima and she took me around and told us some horrendous stories that bring tears to my eyes just thinking about it,&rdquo; recalls Reagan. &ldquo;I told Jim stories she had told me about how walls had collapsed on her and how there was a bright flash and nothing happened, then there was a gust of wind, and it was really hot. It just made it so real to me because this woman I had known had relayed it to me.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<hr style="background-color: rgb(221, 221, 221); color: rgb(221, 221, 221); clear: both; float: none; width: 683px; height: 0.1em; margin: 0px 0px 1.45em; border: none; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 21px;" />\r\n<p style="margin: 0px 0px 1.5em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-size: 14px; font-family: Helvetica, Verdana, ''Lucida Grande'', ''Gill Sans'', Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); line-height: 21px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);">\r\n	<em style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline;">X-Men Character Likenesses TM &amp; &copy; 2012 Marvel Characters, Inc. All rights reserved. TM and &copy; 2012 Twentieth Century Fox Film Corporation. All rights reserved. Not for sale or duplication.</em></p>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n', 'html', 'upload/article/feature/2013/09/26/5243d62110257.jpg', 1, 0, 'Pi', 1, 2, 11, 1, 1380177540, 1380177541, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `{prefix}{module}_article` (`id`, `subject`, `subtitle`, `summary`, `content`, `markup`, `image`, `uid`, `author`, `source`, `pages`, `category`, `status`, `active`, `time_submit`, `time_publish`, `time_update`, `user_update`) VALUES
(12, 'New York City to host NBA All-Star 2015', '', 'NBA All-Star Friday and Saturday Night Events to be held at Barclays Center;\r\n	64th NBA All-Star Game to be played at Madison Square Garden\r\n\r\n	NEW YORK -- New York City has been selected to host NBA All-Star 2015, NBA Commissioner David Stern announced t', '<p>\r\n	<b><i>NBA All-Star Friday and Saturday Night Events to be held at Barclays Center;</i></b><br />\r\n	<span><b><i>64th NBA All-Star Game to be played at Madison Square Garden</i></b></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<b>NEW YORK -- </b>New York City has been selected to host <b>NBA All-Star 2015</b>, NBA Commissioner David Stern announced today. New York City Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg; James L. Dolan, Executive Chairman, The Madison Square Garden Company; Hank J. Ratner, President and CEO, The Madison Square Garden Company; Irina Pavlova, President, ONEXIM Sports and Entertainment Holding USA, Inc.; and Bruce C. Ratner, majority owner and developer of Barclays Center and Executive Chairman of Forest City Ratner Companies, joined Commissioner Stern and Deputy Commissioner Adam Silver for the announcement at the NBA Partner Forum held at Industria Superstudio in New York City.</p>\r\n<div class="IEContainerRinline">\r\n	<div class="IErow">\r\n		&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Your browser does not support iframes.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	The 64th NBA All-Star Game will be played at Madison Square Garden, home of the New York Knicks, on <b>Sunday, Feb.15, 2015</b>. The BBVA Rising Stars Challenge, Sprint NBA All-Star Celebrity Game and State Farm All-Star Saturday Night - including the Sears Shooting Stars, Taco Bell Skills Challenge, Foot Locker Three-Point Contest and Sprite Slam Dunk - will be held at Barclays Center, home of the Brooklyn Nets.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	As part of NBA All-Star 2015, the NBA and its partners will host a variety of community, grassroots and fan events throughout the city&#39;s five boroughs (The Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens and Staten Island). This will mark the fifth time that NBA All-Star will take place in New York, having been held previously at Madison Square Garden in 1954, 1955, 1968 and 1998.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;New York offers an extraordinary opportunity to host NBA All-Star events at two world-class venues,&quot; said Stern. &quot;We look forward to celebrating our game with basketball fans across the entire city, in all five boroughs.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;New York City is the basketball capital of the world and the sport&#39;s biggest stage,&quot; said Mayor Bloomberg. &quot;We&#39;re lucky enough to have two world-class arenas, and the only thing better than having All-Star weekend at Madison Square Garden or the Barclays Center is having it at both of them. The weekend&#39;s activities mean tens of thousands of visitors to the City and lots of activity for local businesses, plus a week of community service events around the five boroughs led by the NBA, which has a terrific record of giving back. We&#39;re thrilled and looking forward to cheering on the stars.&quot;</p>\r\n<div class="IEContainerRinline">\r\n	<div class="IErow">\r\n		&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Your browser does not support iframes.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	For the 13th consecutive year, the 2015 NBA All-Star Game will be televised in primetime on TNT. It will be the 31st year that Turner Sports provides NBA All-Star coverage. The 2015 NBA All-Star Game will be broadcast to a worldwide audience in 215 countries and territories and in more than 40 languages.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;We are honored to host the greatest players in the NBA in the newly transformed World&#39;s Most Famous Arena for the 2015 All-Star Game,&quot; said Dolan. &quot;Over its 134-year history, Madison Square Garden has been privileged to host some of sports most defining and enduring moments and we are thrilled to add this prestigious event to The Garden&#39;s illustrious history. We look forward to working with the City of New York, the NBA and the Brooklyn Nets to make the event a celebration of basketball for all New Yorkers to enjoy.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;We are thrilled to welcome the 2015 NBA All-Star festivities on Friday and Saturday to Barclays Center,&quot; said Brooklyn Nets owner Mikhail Prokhorov. &quot;Brooklyn has produced some of the greatest players in NBA history, so it&#39;s fitting to hold All-Star events in the &#39;Borough of Basketball.&#39; We are looking forward to showing fans and the players a memorable experience in our state-of-the-art venue, and we are also excited to bring the All-Star Game to Barclays Center in the very near future.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;Barclays Center is proud to welcome such an exciting event as All-Star &#39;15 and to continue bringing the best to Brooklyn,&quot; said Bruce C. Ratner. &quot;We are delighted to join with New York City, the NBA and Madison Square Garden for a wonderful weekend. Basketball may have been invented in Springfield, Mass., but its heart and soul are in NYC through and through.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;Madison Square Garden has been a celebrated center of New York since it first opened its doors in 1879. This fall, with the completion of our three-year Transformation, The World&#39;s Most Famous Arena will also become the world&#39;s most state-of-the-art arena,&quot; said Hank Ratner. &quot;2015 will mark our fifth time hosting the All-Star Game, and we look forward to providing yet another unforgettable experience for the great basketball fans of New York.&quot;</p>\r\n<div class="IEContainerRinline">\r\n	<div class="IErow">\r\n		&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Your browser does not support iframes.&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	NBA All-Star is an event with deep roots in New York City, reaching back to the 1954 game (the fourth NBA All-Star Game overall), where the Madison Square Garden faithful saw the Celtics&#39; Bob Cousy tally10 points in overtime en route to MVP honors as the East recorded a 98-93 win over the West. Boston had a second consecutive All-Star Game MVP in 1955 as Bill Sharman scored 10 of his 15 points in the fourth quarter of the East&#39;s 100-91 win over the West in the second NBA All-Star Game played at Madison Square Garden. Philadelphia&#39;s Hal Greer shot 8-of-8 from the floor and notched 21 points during the third NBA All-Star Game played in New York City, a 144-124 East win in 1968. In 1998, the most recent contest in New York, Michael Jordan garnered MVP honors as he scored 23 points and added eight assists and six rebounds during a 135-114 victory for the East.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	NBA All-Star competitions will get underway on Friday, Feb. 13, as the league&#39;s top rookies and second-year players take the court in the BBVA Rising Stars Challenge. Saturday&#39;s festivities will feature State Farm All-Star Saturday Night, an all-inclusive skills showcase comprised of Sears Shooting Stars, a competition featuring NBA and WNBA players, and NBA legends; Taco Bell Skills Challenge, a contest of top guards working against the clock to complete a series of passes, free throws, layups and agility drills; Foot Locker Three-Point Contest, a longstanding staple of the evening; and the high-flying Sprite Slam Dunk. Sunday&#39;s slate of activities will also feature a Sprint Pregame Concert before the 64th NBA All-Star Game tips off.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The NBA will continue to demonstrate its commitment to social responsibility during NBA All-Star 2015 with a full schedule of NBA Cares events. NBA Cares will partner with schools, government and local nonprofit organizations in New York and surrounding areas to highlight the league&#39;s grassroots and community initiatives that reach millions of young people and their parents, while providing critical resources to community-based programs.</p>\r\n', 'html', 'upload/article/feature/2013/09/26/5243d6e28b2c1.jpg', 1, 1, 'Pi', 1, 7, 11, 1, 1380177623, 1380177624, 1380177649, 1),
(13, 'Heat to open training camp in the Bahamas', '', 'MIAMI (AP) --  The Miami Heat are starting this season in the Bahamas.\r\n\r\n	The two-time defending NBA champions are holding training camp at the Atlantis Resort, with practices from Oct. 1 through Oct. 4. The team will fly to the Bahamas on Sept. 30, shor', '<p>\r\n	<strong>MIAMI (AP) -- </strong> The Miami Heat are starting this season in the Bahamas.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The two-time defending NBA champions are holding training camp at the Atlantis Resort, with practices from Oct. 1 through Oct. 4. The team will fly to the Bahamas on Sept. 30, shortly after convening in Miami for the annual media day.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It&#39;s the first time since 2010 that Miami has gone on the road for training camp. That year, the first where LeBron James, Chris Bosh and Dwyane Wade were teammates, the Heat went to a pair of U.S. Air Force installations in Florida&#39;s Panhandle.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Atlantis has converted one of its ballrooms into a basketball court, and now hosts college basketball tournaments annually.</p>\r\n', 'html', '', 1, 4, 'Pi', 1, 7, 11, 1, 1380179136, 1380179139, 0, 0),
(14, 'Wade, Durant tussle on Twitter over rankings', '', 'MIAMI (AP) --  Dwyane Wade and Kevin Durant are getting a little 1-on-1 in before the season starts.\r\n\r\n	Well, on Twitter, anyway.\r\n\r\n	Durant told CineSport in a video interview that he believes his former Oklahoma City teammate James Harden should be con', '<p>\r\n	<strong>MIAMI (AP) -- </strong> Dwyane Wade and Kevin Durant are getting a little 1-on-1 in before the season starts.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Well, on Twitter, anyway.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Durant told CineSport in a video interview that he believes his former Oklahoma City teammate James Harden should be considered one of the top 10 players in the NBA, and Wade -- a three-time NBA champion with the Miami Heat -- should not.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	So Wade responded by posting a message on a social media site Tuesday night that was clearly directed at Durant, saying in part: &quot;Note to self. Make him respect your place in history ... again.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Durant&#39;s tweet in response: &quot;Show me don&#39;t tweet me.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Wade averaged 22.6 points in the 2012 NBA Finals against Durant, Harden and the Thunder. Harden, who now plays for Houston, averaged 12.4 points in that series.</p>\r\n', 'html', '', 1, 4, 'Pi', 1, 7, 11, 1, 1380179207, 1380179209, 1380179698, 1),
(15, 'Ding Wins Historic Final', '', 'Ding Junhui beat Xiao Guodong 10-6 in the first ever all-Chinese ranking final at the Bank of Communications Shanghai Masters.\r\n\r\n	Local hero Ding, from Wuxi not far from Shanghai, delighted his millions of fans by winning the seventh ranking title of his', '<div class="description">\r\n	<a href="/{module}/media/download/id-25" target="_blank"><img src="{upload-url}/media/2013/09/26/25.jpg" /></a></div>\r\n<div class="description">\r\n	Ding Junhui beat Xiao Guodong 10-6 in the first ever all-Chinese ranking final at the Bank of Communications Shanghai Masters.</div>\r\n<p>\r\n	Local hero Ding, from Wuxi not far from Shanghai, delighted his millions of fans by winning the seventh ranking title of his career and second in six months having captured the PTC Grand Finals in March. He received the top prize of &pound;80,000.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Sheffield based Ding, age 26, took his first ranking title on home soil since the 2005 China Open in Beijing. He has often struggled to handle the weight of expectation when he plays in China, but he produced some excellent snooker this week, not least in the final which saw him compile a century and seven more breaks over 50.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	That 2005 Ding victory was the catalyst for the explosion of interest in snooker in China. Since then, increasing numbers of Chinese players have earned places on the professional tour. Prior to this week, only Liang Wenbo had come close to emulating Ding&#39;s success, reaching one ranking final and briefly climbing into the top 16.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Now, Xiao looks the leading candidate to be the &#39;next best&#39; player from mainland China. He is one of the most improved players on the circuit over the past two years and played some superb snooker this week to reach his first ranking final. The 24-year-old Gloucester-based cueman can enjoy his biggest pay-day, &pound;35,000, and look ahead with confidence to the rest of the season.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Ding took the first two frames today with top breaks of 42 and 83, then Xiao made 62 and 67 for 2-2. Ding regained the lead with a 66 before Xiao came from 46-0 down in the sixth to make it 3-3. Ding pulled away at the end of the first session, knocking in 126 and 58 for 5-3 then taking the last frame of the session on the colours.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	On the resumption, Xiao pulled one back with a 78, only for Ding to reel off three frames in a row with 58, 78 and 81 for 9-4. Xiao threatened a fight back as he dominated the next two for 9-6, and led 45-0 in frame 16. But Ding then took his chance with a smooth 71 to seal the title.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;Before the final I knew I needed to build an early lead, and I had to keep my safety strong to force my opponent to give me chances,&quot; said Ding. &quot;I built a three-frame-lead in the afternoon session because Xiao&#39;s safety was not as good as mine. But he managed to play relaxed and open frames in the evening so he did pull some frames back, after I had reached nine. I&#39;m just happy that I managed to win my tenth frame with a solid break.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;Liang Wenbo has been in the final of this tournament too so hopefully there will be many more chances for the players from China. The young generation is growing up quickly so their days will come soon.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;I had to let my emotions go after winning the tournament. This showed how much I wanted this title, I wanted it more than anybody. But there was less pressure on me than in the past when I played here in China.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;I&#39;ve been changing my game a little bit with a friend&#39;s help, and training a lot. Now I can concentrate more on my snooker and this win means a lot to my career.&quot;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Xiao said: &quot;Today is a historic day, no matter whether I won or not. Two Chinese players performing a top class match on worldwide stage. I&#39;m so proud of myself, being a Chinese player. I&#39;ve always dreamed of winning a title but I wasn&#39;t very comfortable out there because this is my first ranking final. I&#39;ll be more relaxed next time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;It&#39;s a special experience for me. I hope not to disappear from sight and hopefully I will take part in many more world class tournaments.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&quot;Before this match my goal was to get into the top 32. I&#39;m in the top 32 now but I hope to raise my ranking steadily. It seems to be really hard for me to get into top 16 this season, but if I keep my form it&#39;s not impossible. I played well in the first few tournaments this season so hopefully I can achieve my goal.&quot;</p>\r\n', 'html', '', 1, 2, 'Pi', 1, 24, 11, 1, 1380179968, 1380179969, 0, 0);
